-- Manchester United Eyes Sevilla’s Moreno, Express Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-11-07T10:57:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/manchester-united-eyes-sevilla-s-moreno-express-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Evra Replacement  Manchester United  may try to sign Sevilla defender Alberto
Moreno to replace  Patrice Evra , the  Daily Express  reported.  Sevilla wants 25 million pounds ($40 million) to release
the 21-year-old Moreno who recently made his debut for Spain,
the Express added.  Sporting Winger  Sporting Lisbon could trade winger Diego Capel to Arsenal,
Liverpool or Tottenham for 6 million pounds in January, the
 Daily Express  reported.  Capel is one of the highest earners on Sporting’s payroll
and the team is seeking to cut its costs, the Express said.  Dutch Target  Manchester City is interested in hiring Dutch-Serbian
winger Richairo Zivkovic from Groningen, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  Liverpool is also scouting the 17-year-old who has been
compared to Arjen Robben, the Mirror said.  City Exit  Everton, Newcastle, Hull and Crystal Place want to sign
midfielder Abdisalam Ibrahim, who is free to leave  Manchester
City  in January, the  Daily Star  reported.  The 22-year-old is currently on loan in Norway, the Star
said. 